{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "18", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "10", "M": "29", "S": "39"}}, "news": [{"title": "Lucknow development body launches OTS for around 4,000 defaulters", "para": "The Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) is launching a One-Time Settlement (OTS) program to aid approximately 4,000 defaulters. This initiative offers relief from penalties and compound interest, allowing allottees to regularize ownership by clearing dues. Applications will be processed within three months, with a 3% rebate for full payments made within 30 days.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/lucknow-development-authority-introduces-one-time-settlement-plan-for-4000-defaulting-property-owners/130351522?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-65720/130351522.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Surat: Pragya Nagar won\u2019t be charged property tax", "para": "Surat Municipal Corporation has waived property tax for residents of Pragya Nagar after their homes were demolished in 2025. The civic body took this step after residents received tax bills for the upcoming year, despite their colony no longer existing.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/surat-residents-of-pragya-nagar-exempt-from-property-tax-following-demolition/130351468?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-96144/130351468.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "GVMC initiates comprehensive slum survey across Visakhapatnam", "para": "The Greater Visakhapatnam Municipal Corporation (GVMC) is conducting a comprehensive survey of 66 slums to assess development levels. Slums meeting certain criteria will be denotified, while others, like Velampeta and Indira Nagar, will undergo redevelopment through a public-private partnership. This initiative aims to transform the city into a slum-free zone with new high-rise residential apartments.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/gvmc-launches-slum-survey-for-redevelopment-in-visakhapatnam/130351400?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-23118/130351400.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}